source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/saucy-ginger-chicken-and-rice-6765a76b40dbba16e1c1cc42
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim stem ends off @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; halve widthwise.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

In @oven-ready aluminum tray{1}, combine chicken, green beans, a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Bake, uncovered, on top rack until green beans are tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{12-16%minutes}.

When chicken and green beans have about 3 minutes left, place @microwavable rice{1} in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Add @water{3%tbsp}, cover tightly with @plastic wrap{}, and microwave until warmed through, ~{1 1/2-2%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Once chicken is done, remove tray from oven. Carefully pour @stir-fry sauce{3%ounce} over chicken and green beans; stir to combine. Crush @peanuts{1/2%ounce} in their bag.

Divide rice and chicken and green beans between shallow bowls in separate sections. Sprinkle chicken and green beans with peanuts and drizzle with as much @sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.